{
  "stem": "11272.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the thing that I remember mostly about the ghetto is the humiliation that they put us through, forcing us to throw bricks at each other-- catch 'em our bare hands.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and I went back because I remember how rough those bricks were-- how it took my skin off.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after about an hour or two, I had no skin left on my hand.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And God forbid, if you dropped a brick, the SS men were there to trample over you or maybe even shoot you.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a very painful memory that I invoked when I went back, how horrible it was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because after they forced us to throw all the brick and pack it up in the end of the ghetto, when it was through, they forced us to, to throw them back again and stack them up on the other end.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did they make the women and girls do this as well?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, but they made them do some humiliating things-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] washing mud clothing, just nothing but to humiliate them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They gave us nothing to eat except what we brought with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, you know, after a couple days, the food started running out, you know, because we weren't prepared for it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They finally gave us a little bit of bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One evening, one of the neighbors, who was a very dear friend, he came and threw us over some food because he knew we were-- we had no food at all with a little note.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he says, I pray for you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's a non-Jewish neighbor, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, it was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I also remember my dearest, dearest friend from the village, Jonczi, across the street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He and I were inseparable.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
